.TH "cma_alloc" 9 "cma_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cma_alloc \- allocate pages from contiguous area
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct page *" cma_alloc
.BI "(struct cma *cma "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ","
.BI "unsigned int align "  ","
.BI "bool no_warn "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cma" 12
Contiguous memory region for which the allocation is performed.
.IP "count" 12
Requested number of pages.
.IP "align" 12
Requested alignment of pages (in PAGE_SIZE order).
.IP "no_warn" 12
Avoid printing message about failed allocation
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function allocates part of contiguous memory on specific
contiguous memory area.
